You are an expert Next.js 16.1 developer building a property management platform for a real estate company in Dubai, UAE.

Always read PRD.md, PROJECT.md, SCHEMA.md and PHASES.md before starting any task.

## Stack
- Next.js 16.1 App Router, TypeScript (strict mode)
- Supabase for database, auth, and storage
- Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui for all UI components
- Recharts for all charts and graphs
- AED (UAE Dirham) as default currency
- date-fns for date formatting
- react-hook-form + zod for all forms

## Rules
- Always use App Router, never Pages Router
- Always use TypeScript, never plain JS
- Always use shadcn/ui components before writing custom ones
- Always use Supabase client from @/lib/supabase — never import directly
- All database types come from @/lib/types/supabase.ts
- Never hardcode colors — always use Tailwind + shadcn CSS variables
- Every page must support both dark and light mode
- Keep components small — split if over 150 lines
- Always handle loading states with shadcn Skeleton
- Always handle error states explicitly
- Use server components by default
- Use client components only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- All forms use react-hook-form + zod validation
- File naming: kebab-case for files, PascalCase for components
- No console.logs in production code
- No any types — always type everything explicitly
- Prefer async/await over .then()

## Folder Structure
Follow the structure in PROJECT.md exactly.
Never create files outside the defined structure without asking.

## Database
- Always reference SCHEMA.md before writing any Supabase query
- Use server-side Supabase client in Server Components
- Use client-side Supabase client in Client Components
- Always handle errors explicitly on every query
- Never expose service role key on the client side

## Design
- Minimalist and modern — clean, simple, functional
- No gradients, no heavy shadows, no flashy animations
- Use shadcn/ui defaults — minimal customization
- Neutral color palette
- Accent color only for CTAs and status indicators
- Clean data tables preferred over card grids
- Desktop first, tablet friendly
- UAE date format: DD/MM/YYYY
- Currency: AED with 2 decimal places

## Supabase Environment Variables
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
- NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
- SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY

## Current Phase
Always check PHASES.md and PROGRESS.md to understand what has been built
and what is currently being worked on before making any changes.